{{Main|William Wei}}
Taiwanese singer-songwriter [[William Wei]] has held three concerts. His debut concert, The Fleeing of a Two-Legged Bookcase, was held at [[Taipei]] and [[Taichung]] in 2010.<ref name="Concert-The-Fleeing-Of-A-Two-Legged-Bookcase">{{cite web|title=年代售票 - [兩腳書櫥的逃亡]韋禮安演唱會 |url=https://www.ticket.com.tw/dm.asp?P1=0000011024 |website=ticket.com.tw |accessdate=May 23, 2016 |publisher=ERAticket |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hiipfyra?url=https://www.ticket.com.tw/dm.asp?P1=0000011024 |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The concert was held in support of his [[William Wei (album) |first eponymous album]].
In 2012, Wei held his second concert, Through My Lenses, in [[Hong Kong]] and later [[Taiwan]].<ref name="Concert-Through-My-Lenses">{{cite web|title=韦礼安&quot;Through my Lenses&quot;印象派演唱会 - Timable |url=http://timable.com/zh-cn/event/69059 |website=timable.com |accessdate=May 23, 2016 |publisher=Timable |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hijEGqsM?url=http://timable.com/zh-cn/event/69059 |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> In 2015, Wei held his third concert, Free That Girl, at the [[Taipei Arena]] of [[Taiwan]].<ref name="Concert-Free-The-Girl">{{cite web |title=臺北小巨蛋 ─ 2015/09/12《2015韋禮安 放開那女孩演唱會》 |url=http://www.arena.taipei/ct.asp?xItem=105952899&ctNode=62590&mp=12203a |website=arena.taipei.com |accessdate=May 23, 2016 |publisher=Taipei Arena |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hijLXSuG?url=http://www.arena.taipei/ct.asp?xItem=105952899&ctNode=62590&mp=12203a |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The concert's opening act was a 15-minute Broadway style sing-and-dance item that infused elements of swing jazz and disco dance.<ref>{{cite web|title=不只是女孩！放开你所有感官吧－韦礼安“放开那女孩”演唱会 - KKBOX |url=https://www.kkbox.com/sg/en/column/live_reviews-43-67-1.html |website=kkbox.com |accessdate=May 24, 2016 |publisher=KKBOX |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hiugpIve?url=https://www.kkbox.com/sg/en/column/live_reviews-43-67-1.html |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> Free That Girl was held in [[Hong Kong]] on 18 June 2016.<ref name="Concert-Free-The-Girl-HK">{{cite web|title=Weibird Free That Girl Live - Hong Kong |url=http://www.hkticketing.com/events/KBWEIBI0616 |website=hkticketing.com |accessdate=May 23, 2016 |publisher=HK Ticketing |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hiuvsc7u?url=http://www.hkticketing.com/events/KBWEIBI0616 |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Major concerts== ===The Fleeing of a Two-Legged Bookcase (2010) ===
The Fleeing of a Two-Legged Bookcase (兩腳出書的逃亡) was Wei's first major concert.<ref name="Concert-The-Fleeing-Of-A-Two-Legged-Bookcase"/> It was held in support of his first eponymous album. Wei performed songs from his debut album as well as three previously unreleased songs: 'Why Life', 'She'll be an Angel' and 'Me, a Pig, and His Girlfriend'.<ref name="KKBOX">{{cite web|title=「韦礼安 (William Wei) - “两脚书橱的逃亡”演唱会Live - KKBOX |url=https://www.kkbox.com/my/en/album/cviVeMKYKr4xyew0Fy4c008l-index.html |website=KKBOX.com |publisher=KKBOX |accessdate=May 24, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hiwBBIC7?url=https://www.kkbox.com/my/en/album/cviVeMKYKr4xyew0Fy4c008l-index.html |archivedate=May 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> An accompanying [[The Fleeing of a Two-Legged Bookcase (Live Album)|live album]] of the same name was released on 3 June 2011. <ref name="KKBOX"/> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;" |- ! width="150px" | Date ! width="150px" | City ! width="150px" | Country ! width="150px" | Venue ! width="150px" | Special Guest(s) ! Ref |- |18 September 2010 | [[Taipei]] |rowspan="2" | [[Taiwan]] | [[Taipei International Convention Center]] | | <ref name="Concert-The-Fleeing-Of-A-Two-Legged-Bookcase"/> |- |25 September 2010 | [[Taichung]] | [[National Chung Hsing University]] Hui Sun Auditorium | | <ref name="Concert-The-Fleeing-Of-A-Two-Legged-Bookcase"/> |- |}
===Through My Lenses (2012) === Through My Lenses (印象派) was Wei's second major concert. It was held in support of his second album. The concert was first held in Hong Kong<ref name="Concert-Through-My-Lenses"/> and it was Wei's first major concert abroad. The concert was later held in Taiwan.<ref name="Concert-Through-My-Lenses"/>
